answers.answer: I know you've probably heard this before, but everyone's different and sometimes conception does take that long.  Has your husband/partner been tested.  Is he overweight, have diabetes or does he regularly consume alchohol (2-3 drinks/day).  These can greatly affect his sperms' motility.  My sister-in-law had this same issue.  Everything was normal with her.  Her husband assumed that since he was ejaculating, that the sperm was healthy.  He was about 40lbs overweight with diabetes.  After 5 years of trying, he finally decided to lose weight, He got checked and found that his sperm count was a little low and had low motility.  He continued to lose weight, which helped his diabetes and sperm count.  The next year, they got pregnant.  My coworker tried for 6 years and got pregnant after whe and her husband stopped trying and started adoption procedures.  Have your husband/partner checked out and good luck.

question: I am a 29-year-old female and when i was 23-years-old i had a ectopic pregnancy. I haven't been able to concieve yet. I've been to doctor's and everything is normal. Does it take this long to concieve or is something really wrong with me?
title: Charlene
